00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:12.200
Hello!
In this new immunopill

00:00:12.274 --> 00:00:15.020
we are going to continue 
with the lymphocyte subpopulations.

00:00:15.177 --> 00:00:18.205
As I have explained before, 
they are going to serve as a reference

00:00:18.285 --> 00:00:20.670
before studying
 the antigen receptor of the T lymphocyte.

00:00:20.925 --> 00:00:23.900
In this pill, we are paying attention
to the main subpopulation,

00:00:24.022 --> 00:00:28.170
the most evolved T lymphocytes: 
the alpha beta T lymphocytes.

00:00:28.742 --> 00:00:33.170
We have this situation: we have already studied
the gamma delta lymphocytes; they are a minority;

00:00:33.394 --> 00:00:37.720
they are called T1 by some authors
and have specific functions

00:00:38.228 --> 00:00:41.670
because they include delta 1 and delta 2 chains;
I remind you they fight against tumors.

00:00:41.771 --> 00:00:46.620
And they also have the CD8 co-receptor,
which is the alpha alpha co-receptor.

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:49.220
What happens with the alpha beta cells?

00:00:49.531 --> 00:00:53.920
From the point of view of their activity
we normally call them

00:00:54.057 --> 00:00:56.800
cooperative and cytotoxic,
and approximately

00:00:56.891 --> 00:00:59.050
all the proportions we can see here
are right.

00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:04.537
About 60% of our alpha beta cells 
in blood are cooperative

00:01:04.651 --> 00:01:07.050
and about 40% are cytotoxic.

00:01:07.222 --> 00:01:14.300
In fact, these names are incomplete, 
porque, as we will see in this immunopill,

00:01:14.411 --> 00:01:17.020
apart from the cooperative function
there are some other functions

00:01:17.154 --> 00:01:20.300
inside the cells expressing
CD4 proteins

00:01:20.570 --> 00:01:24.270
Similarly, apart from the cytotoxic function
there are also some other functions

00:01:24.468 --> 00:01:27.600
inside the cells expressing
CD8 proteins.

00:01:27.737 --> 00:01:31.400
So, it would be more correct 
to use CD4 and CD8

00:01:31.540 --> 00:01:34.080
rather than talking 
about cooperative and cytotoxic cells.

00:01:34.280 --> 00:01:37.080
However, it is a convention 
that many immunologists use.

00:01:37.480 --> 00:01:43.100
The CD8 of these alpha beta cells
is mainly the evolved CD8.

00:01:43.348 --> 00:01:46.731
The CD8 alpha beta 
has a chain of every type;

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:50.920
there is a disulfide bond between them;
But a little proportion of cells

00:01:51.097 --> 00:01:54.300
can still express 
the old co-receptor: the alpha alpha.

00:01:54.514 --> 00:01:58.170
we have seen before that this co-receptor
was the one expressed by gamma delta lymphocytes.

00:01:59.920 --> 00:02:03.450
Let's focus on cytotoxic lymphocytes,

00:02:03.554 --> 00:02:06.550
that is, those that express CD8.

00:02:06.811 --> 00:02:09.320
What type of cells are these?

00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:14.420
From the point of view of their activation,
both CD4 and CD8,

00:02:14.594 --> 00:02:17.000
if we analyze them 
in people like you,

00:02:17.097 --> 00:02:20.970
healthy adults, we will see 
they appear in the same proportion.

00:02:21.154 --> 00:02:24.950
Half of them are virgins or naive,
and half of them are memory cells.

00:02:25.165 --> 00:02:27.820
These proportions gradually change 
according to age.

00:02:28.022 --> 00:02:32.000
So a new-born has 
100% of virgin cells

00:02:32.125 --> 00:02:33.850
and no memory cells.

00:02:34.274 --> 00:02:38.520
As we grow up,
we contact with pathogens,

00:02:38.651 --> 00:02:43.170
and naturally these virgin cells gradually 
seem to show characteristics of memory cells

00:02:43.280 --> 00:02:45.000
and these proportions start to change.

00:02:45.280 --> 00:02:49.817
We would reach old age 
with a vast majority of memory cells.

00:02:49.908 --> 00:02:56.970
They will never be 100% because
 we will never contact all the antigens

00:02:57.085 --> 00:02:58.720
against which we are prepared.

00:02:58.853 --> 00:03:01.450
So, we will always have
virgin cells,

00:03:01.520 --> 00:03:04.750
no matter how old the person is.

